div.p:
And all Marriages shall be Registred by the Town Clerk of the same Town where they are consummated;
   Town Clerk to Register Marriages.
 and every Justice or Minister as aforesaid, shall return a Note or Certificate unto the Clerk of the Town of the names of all Persons which they shall Marry, and of the time when, within three Months at farthest after Consummation of the same, and shall allow and pay out of his Fee unto the Clerk for Entring the same three pence: Any Law, Usage or Custom to the contrary notwithstanding.

That if any Man shall wear Womens Apparrel; or if any Woman shall wear Mens Apparrel, and be thereof duely Convicted;
                  Penalty on Men or Women that shall wear contrary Apparrel.
                they shall be Corporally Punished or Fined, at the discretion of the Quarter Sessions, not exceeding Five Pounds, to the use of the County where the Offence is Committed, towards the defraying of the County Charges.

That the Act Entituled, An Act for the giving Succours and Assistance to the Neighbouring Provinces and Colonies against His Majesties Enemies;
                  Succours & Assistances to the Neighbouring Provinces.
                made and passed in the Seventh Year of His present Majesties Reign, and all the Powers, Provisions, Articles, Clauses, Matters and Things therein contained, shall continue and be in full force and Effect, unto the end of the next Session of the General Assembly, and no longer.
